metadata.name: Traveling Circus #47
metadata.description:
A fun little project for the bear market.  Flow lines and shapes move between two flow fields.  Made in p5.js.  Finishes off using Dave Pagurek's grain shader.  For main shape color from palette, color #6 is sometimes best.  The code will mint exactly what you create with the parameters, while another minter will get a different result with the same parameters. 

Press "s" to save a 3500 x 3500 pixel png.

metadata.name: Primordial #195
metadata.description:
Primordial is a study of abstract forms. The algorithm, written in p5.js and WebGL, utilizes domain warping to create twisted fields of color and then overlays thousands of tiny lines to provide depth and texture. The outputs are chaotic but not completely formless, like a swirling mass of plasma from the early universe, or a strange proto-life form suspended in prehistoric ooze.

CONTROLS:

1-9: Increase resolution and save image in PNG format

B: Toggle borders on/off

F: Fullscreen
P: Portrait
L: Landscape
S: Square

For third party license information, please see license.md

David Brice Allen
October 2022

metadata.name: Flowers and Sky #210
metadata.description:
Flowers and Sky

Using natural brushstrokes and bright colors, this generative system creates stunning scenes of flower-filled meadows under a brilliant sky. It is inspired by the masters of impressionist art and aims to capture the beauty of nature.

Every leaf, petal, cloud, and sunray are generated from code using simulated brushstrokes. The flowers and trees are suggestive only and do not depict real species.

There are 8 formal features that have many values in order to generate a wide variety of outputs. The only rare feature is a SkyMode of 'Eclipse' which occurs in 3% of the outputs.

--------------------------

This is a 100% code generated project. Outputs are created at a default resolution of 1500 x 1000.

Click on the output and use these keys to change the resolution or save the output:
's' - save at current resolution

'2' - change to  3000 x 2000 resolution
'3' - change to  4500 x 3000 resolution
...
'8' - change to 12000 x 8000 resolution

URL Parameters: You can also set the resolution in the url.
To change the resolution append &res=2 (or 3-8)

Copyright 2023 Jeff Clark

metadata.name: Distant Views #118
metadata.description:
This work explores generative way of painting landscapes on canvas. Algorithm uses backward moves with big polygon brush to produce mountain-like structures. Shades of randomly selected color make illusion of distance and adds to diversity of terrain. Sun and Moon can have different positions on the horizon or not be visible at all. Their color changes depending on the position. Besides night and day, there are three rough variants of composition based on percentage that sky takes on canvas. There is a also chance to have snowy mountain on top.

Artwork was created using p5js.

@VolatileMoods

December, 2021.

metadata.name: Siren #404
metadata.description:
In the book "The Art of Computer Designing", Osamu Sato illustrates how unexpected shapes emerge when a shape that is the color of the background, overlaps a shape that is a different color. I kept this in mind while experimenting with an algorithm by bobsarea that divides any circle by N. 

Siren produces each output by taking (rings, lines, and points) of either (red, black, or white) in sizes ranging from (small to large), and placing them around the perimeter of a centered circle N times in (randomized distances) from the center, on a background of (red, black, or white).

2022 (CC0 1.0)
